    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9603" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάρις</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ιτος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαίρω</span>, cf. gratia):
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">quality of pleasing, grace, charm, charms</span>, pl., <i><span class="en">Od. 6.237</span></i>; then <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">favor, thanks,
            gratitude;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φέρειν τινι</span>, ‘confer,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 5.211</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀρέσθαι</span>, ‘earn’; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δοῦναι, ἴδμεναι</span>, ‘thank,’ ‘be grateful,’
            <i><span class="en">Il. 14.235</span></i>.—Acc. as adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χάριν</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">for the sake of</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινός</span>, i. e. to please him, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.744</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
